Initializeation of BAP LSG functionality.

Invoked in stateIL2_init state. This function respond for initialize BAP LSG functionality sending InitSenBuffer requests with current BAP properities, enabling BAP communication and postponing handling of BAP requests if needed.
reentrant No
The IL2_state have to be set to stateIL2_init state.
N/A
void
void
Globals
[in] di58_IL2_BAPTaskCounter [in, out] initialization_setup_state [out] IL2_state
Input->Output-Correlation
If initialization was not done yet ( initialization_setup_state is FALSE) and BAP communication is disabled, initialize BAPHandler_IL2 by sending InitSenBuffer requests with current BAP properities and in case of success initialization_setup_state will be set to TRUE. If initialisation was already done ( initialization_setup_state is not FALSE) but BAP communication is disabled, enable it and verify the need to pospone handling BAP requests for (at least) 50ms. If di58_IL2_BAPTaskCounter elapsed, IL2_state is set to stateIL2_run state, otherwise it is set to stateIL2_waitForBap state.
Call Sequence
Test Method
SWATT unit tests. The testing method is described in: IL2_initialize

Basic operation mode of BAPHandler_IL2.

Invoked in stateIL2_run state. If BAP communication is enabled, personalization functionality will be handled (if personalization funcitonality is active) and adaptations and codings will be updated (when couter AdaptandCodingCounter elapses) as well as all InteriorLight2 properities. Then updated data will be synchinized and stored in NvM. If BAP communication is disabled, BAPHandler_IL2 will be forced to go to stateIL2_init state.
reentrant No
The IL2_state have to be set to stateIL2_run state.
N/A
void
void
Globals
[in] di58_PSO_ImExport [in, out] persoStatus [in, out] di58_IL2_AdaptAndCodingCounter [out] initialization_setup_state [out] IL2_state
Input->Output-Correlation
If BAP communication is disabled, invoke reinitialisation by setting initialization_setup_state to 0, IL2_state to stateIL2_init and indication the remote services have to be stoped. If BAP communication is enabled, handle personalisation functionality (the activation of the functionality is verified by checking defined elements from structure IL2_AdaptCodings), increment counter di58_IL2_AdaptAndCodingCounter by 1, then verify it elapsed. If so, invoke functions responsible for checking adaptations and codings and unpading parameters of InteriorLight2 and reset the couter. Then invoke funtion responsieble for update of the data.
Call Sequence

SWATT unit tests. The testing method is described in: IL2_run

Checks if conditions for BAP function list has changed.

Invoked in: IL2_run This function verify adaptations and condings responsible for activating functionalities on the FunctionList. If any of such variables changes, FunctionList will be recalculated and BAP comunication will be reinitilized.
reentrant No
N/A

[out] IL2_state
Input->Output-Correlation
Actual adaptation or coding is stored in IL2_AdaptCodings. It is compared with data from structures IL2_AdaptCodings_old, and if it has changed, structure IL2_AdaptCodings is updated, and additionaly in case of personalized parameter, default flags are set in structure IL2_PIM_PSO_Parameters. In case of any change, the need of recalcutae the FunctionList will be marked in di58_PSO_ImExport, BAP communication will be disabled and BAPHandler_IL2 will be initilized in next cycle ( initialization_setup_state and IL2_state will be set to proper states).
